summary: Thanos is the protagonist
title: Thanos is the protagonist
body:
[Avengers: Infinity Wars end screen that says “Thanos will return”

- Thanos has a goal and everyone else is trying to stop him

- Thanos will return, instead of “The Avengers”

- The other characters were only filmed so that we would know why Thanos was struggling so much because otherwise it would look like the writers just hated Thanos

tags: rewatching stuff just makes me think
tony has a big part to play i thino
enough of a part that stephen felt the need to save him
summary:
Tony: I wasn't tricked, I was shown; it wasn't a nightmare, it was my legacy--the end of the path I started us on.
Nick: You...
body:
Tony: I wasn’t tricked, I was shown; it wasn’t a nightmare, it was my legacy–the end of the path I started us on.

Nick: You come up with some pretty impressive inventions, Tony. War isn’t one of them.

Tony: I watched my friends die. You’d think that’d be as bad as it gets, right? Heh. Nope… it wasn’t the worst part.

Nick: The worst part… is that you didn’t.

This dialogue from Age of Ultron is fucking scary, considering Infinity War–considering that Tony watched more than half of his friends evaporate into dust. I think this is foreshadowing what’s to come? Because like, why did Stephen save Tony, of all people? Why just him, why not give up the stone before that? To save others? Why is Tony so significant that Stephen waited until almost everyone died to save just him???

Because he’s going to be the last one standing in the end.
